(Executive answer: Data on education in France includes indicators of social segregation in middle schools and information on higher education applications via Parcoursup. The dataset "Indicateurs de ségrégation sociale entre collčges dans les départements" \(1452 rows analyzed, covering 2014-2024\) shows that the total number of middle schools \(`nb_coll_calcul`\) ranges from 8 to 6957, with a mean of 156.84 and a median of 69. Public middle schools \(`nb_coll_PU_calcul`\) constitute a significant portion, with a strong linear relationship \(R^2=0.999206\) to the total number of schools. The percentage of very favorable social categories \(`p_tfav`\) in all middle schools averages 21.08%, while in public middle schools \(`p_tfav_pu`\) it is 18.03%, and in private middle schools \(`p_tfav_pr`\) it is 35.61%. The average number of middle schools has remained relatively stable between 2014 and 2024, fluctuating around 156-158. For higher education, the "Parcoursup 2025" dataset contains 14252 records detailing student applications and institutional responses.) Tj
